Curry Chicken Soup with Cocnut and Kale 
  --Cook's Country
  
3 tbsp evoo
1 onion, chopped
1 red bell pepper, stemmed, seeded, and chopped
2 tbsp grated fresh ginger
1 tbsp curry powder
1 1/2 tsp table salt
1/4 tsp cayenne pepper + extra for seasoning
8 oz kale, stemmed and chopped
1 1/2 lb boneless, skinless chicken thighs, trimmed and cut into 1‚ÅÑ2" chunks
2 c water
14 oz can coconut milk
1 tbsp lime juice, plus lime wedges for serving

Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium-high heat until shimmering. Add onion and bell pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and beginning to brown, 6-8 min. Add ginger, curry powder, salt, and cayenne and cook until fragrant, ~1 min. Stir in kale, chicken, water, and coconut milk and bring to boil, scraping up any fond. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until chicken is cooked through and kale is tender, about 15 minutes. Off heat, stir in lime juice and season with salt and extra cayenne to taste. Serve, passing lime wedges separately.
